Police have on Thursday morning arrested Tiaty legislator William Kamket.
The MP confirmed to the Nation that he is currently being held at the Kileleshwa police station in Nairobi.
The MP's lawyers and some of his supporters have arrived at the station.
Officers are limiting the number of persons coming to the station over the case to one per vehicle.



